data.content:
Once upon a time in a small village nestled deep in the mountains, there lived a young and ambitious boy named Lucas. From a very young age, Lucas had always dreamt of exploring the world beyond his village, yearning for adventure and excitement. But, as the youngest of eight siblings in a poor family, he was always expected to help with their struggling farm and had little time for his own aspirations.

One sunny morning, Lucas decided that he couldn't wait any longer. He packed a small bag with his few belongings, bid farewell to his family, and set off on a journey that would change his life forever. Determined to prove himself and find his place in the world, he ventured into the dense and mysterious forest that surrounded his village.

As Lucas delved deeper into the forest, the trees seemed to whisper ancient secrets, guiding him towards an unknown destiny. He followed their lead, traversing treacherous terrain, overcoming obstacles, and encountering mystical creatures along the way.

Days turned into weeks, and Lucas found himself emerging from the enchanted forest into a lively and bustling city. It was a place filled with diversity, inventions, and endless possibilities. With wide eyes and an eager heart, Lucas realized that he had finally arrived at the place where he could make his dreams come true.

Lucas was captivated by the city's vibrancy and decided to stay, finding odd jobs to sustain himself. He worked tirelessly during the day and spent nights wandering the city, awed by its grandeur. One fateful evening, while strolling through a park, Lucas stumbled upon an open-air theater and was enchanted by the marvelous production he witnessed. It was a story of love, bravery, and redemption that stirred something deep within him.

Driven by a newfound passion for the arts, Lucas dedicated himself to learning everything about acting and storytelling. Through persistence and sheer talent, he secured an audition for an esteemed theater company that would make or break his dreams of success. Nervously stepping onto the stage, Lucas poured all his heart into his audition piece, captivating everyone with his raw emotion and powerful delivery.

Days turned into weeks of anticipation, and finally, a letter arrived for Lucas - an invitation to join the theater company. Overcome with joy, Lucas embraced his new life as a performer, taking the stage each night, regaling audiences with his passionate performances and winning hearts with his charismatic persona.

News of Lucas's talent spread like wildfire, not just within the city but far beyond. He became a renowned actor, captivating audiences around the world with his riveting performances. Through his craft, Lucas became a voice for the voiceless, shining a light on societal injustices and inspiring countless individuals to believe in their dreams.

Years later, Lucas returned to his village, now a celebrated hero. He shared his stories, his triumphs, and his failures with his family and fellow villagers. Lucas's journey from a small village boy to a revered actor had not only transformed his own life but had ignited a spark of hope and possibility within the hearts of the villagers.

And so, Lucas's tale continues to inspire generations, reminding everyone that with unwavering determination, open hearts, and the courage to chase their dreams, anything is possible.

prompts.name: prompt_1
prompts.input: Tell me a joke about apples

data.content:
Why did the apple go to school?

Because it wanted to be a "smarty-pie"!

prompts.name: prompt_2
prompts.input: Tell this joke in a shakespearean rhetoric

data.content:
Why did the noble apple venture forth to the halls of learning?

Forsooth! It did aspire to become a "smarty-pie"!
